Attention! Mr. Todsaphon, grade 9, room 1,
please report to the principal's office immediately.

234
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:05,800
Attention! Mr. Todsaphon, grade 9/1
please report to the principal's office immediately.

235
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,080
Come in, Todsaphon!

236
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,560
Here’s your chance to confess.

237
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,680
What were you up to sneaking into the science lab?

238
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:01,280
Well, I...

239
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:08,040
This boy is a tutor close to Tod.

240
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,920
He came to visit at home that day.

241
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:12,880
Tod's mother asked him to visit Tod at school.

242
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:17,720
That's not the point here, sir.

243
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:22,080
Your son was bringing an outsider, who is not a school staff, inside.

244
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:25,200
You saw the video, right?

245
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:28,200
Yes, I watched it.

246
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:33,200
But I don't see these two doing anything more than
just sitting and chatting.

247
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,200
What are you trying to imply?

248
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:39,040
You're defending your son in the wrong way.

249
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:43,720
The actions of your son in this video...

250
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:48,040
don't seem to be just brotherly, as you think.

251
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,320
And also... lifting the legs to apply the ointment like this,

252
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,880
you think that's normal behavior?

253
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,480
This is too much.

254
00:22:57,120 --> 00:23:01,400
You're implying something more than what we can see.

255
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:06,560
And as I said, that man is like a real brother to Tod.

256
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:10,280
Regarding sneaking into the room without permission,

257
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,360
it’s wrong, I agree.

258
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,720
If you want to punish my son for that,

259
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,560
it's understandable.

260
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,880
But let's not dive into baseless speculation.

261
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,720
I know my son.

262
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:26,440
If we just imagine and blame children like this,

263
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,560
how can we be good adults?

264
00:23:58,240 --> 00:24:02,080
Honestly, you didn't need to defend me.

265
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:10,320
Even if the principal or you had criticized me,
it wouldn't have affected me.

266
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,440
I knew it wouldn't bother you.

267
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:17,360
But I don't see any reason to scold you.

268
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:22,160
Hearing the principal say that stuff... just made me think,

269
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:25,560
what era are we in now?

270
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:32,920
I'm really your son, aren't I?

271
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:38,280
-You mean that in a good way, right?
-Of course!

272
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,400
Where's mom today?

273
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,880
Why did you come instead?

274
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:50,240
She's at Nick's mom's funeral in Chiang Mai.

275
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,200
But she'll be back tonight.

276
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:57,120
Oh, Nick asked me not to tell mom and dad.

277
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:00,600
Has mom talked to Nick?

278
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,880
She went without telling Nick either.

279
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:08,320
She tried calling since morning but got no response.

280
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:11,760
She's just as worried about Nick as you are.

281
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:16,440
I know you've always wanted an older brother.

282
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:20,680
Your feelings for Nick are just brotherly,
right? Not what the principal implied.

283
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:28,440
Your mom always says I don't pay enough attention to you.

284
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:31,160
But I want you to know;

285
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:34,160
although I am not always attentive

286
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:37,680
it doesn't mean I don't care about you.

287
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:42,960
My son is so headstrong.

288
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,960
So hard-headed that I don't know if there's any water in there

289
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,200
since it never seems to leak out.

290
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:56,360
Shall we follow mom to see Nick?

291
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:59,080
How much is a flight?

292
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:04,440
You should head back to class.

293
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:05,520
I've got to get to work.

294
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:07,600
See you at home.

295
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:34,480
[Khon Kaen (KKC) > Chiang Mai (CNX) 3,820 baht.]

296
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,720
-Everything okay there?
-Yeah.

297
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,480
He's left with just his brother.

298
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,480
It’s just very sad though.

299
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:45,040
Here, Nick sent these for you.

300
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:53,520
Give Nick some time, alright?

301
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:59,080
He asked you to focus on your exams.

302
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:05,520
We've talked about letting you move to Bangkok with him.

303
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:11,520
If you pass the exam, you can go there.

304
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,000
Really, mom?

305
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:18,200
Yes, but pass the exam first.

306
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:24,080
After tonight, mom and dad can go to bed first.

307
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,880
I'll sleep on the sofa here.

308
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,960
I’ll study harder to pass the exam.

309
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:44,840
[T.O.D.: Everything will be okay, bro! I'm always here for you, always supporting you.]

310
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:56,000
[One Month Later]

311
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:11,160
[T.O.D.: Heading into the exam now.]
[Pluto: I'm teaching until 6, will call you right after.]

312
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:16,760
5:57 p.m.

313
00:28:17,160 --> 00:28:20,920
5:58 p.m.

314
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:24,560
5:59 p.m.

315
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:26,920
6:00 p.m.

316
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:30,400
Hey, Nick. Just got out of my exam

317
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,240
How'd it go?

318
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,680
Almost didn't finish,

319
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:35,120
but I managed to complete it.

320
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,040
See, I told you.

321
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:40,280
Without your help last week,

322
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:42,200
I might not have made it.

323
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:45,080
Done teaching for the day?

324
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:48,880
Actually, I ended up not teaching today. The student cancelled.

325
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,960
Oh, why's that?

326
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:55,120
I'm currently looking at new condos.
Will send you pictures of the room soon.

327
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:56,520
Really?

328
00:28:57,800 --> 00:29:00,120
So, Champ didn't move, did he?

329
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:03,040
Does that mean you're moving out instead?

330
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:05,520
Not exactly.

331
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:08,240
Right now, I don't think Champ will bother me for a bit.

332
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,800
Just for a bit?

333
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:13,160
So, he might come back to bother you?

334
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:17,200
By the way, which area are you looking in?

335
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:19,720
Pick somewhere near my school.

336
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:20,960
I don't want a long walk.

337
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:23,320
And I'd rather not wake up too early.

338
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:25,560
I'm scouting near your school,

339
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:28,280
but also considering other areas.

340
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,600
I haven’t decided to move yet,

341
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:32,240
need to save a bit more.

342
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,240
Thinking about getting a loan this time,

343
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:36,400
seems like a good investment.

344
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:43,560
If I move there, I’ll ask my parents to help with your expenses.

345
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:47,040
No worries. I've got it all planned out,

346
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,840
including stuff for you.

347
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:57,920
Tod, I've made my decision.

348
00:29:58,360 --> 00:30:00,160
I’m not going to America.

349
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:02,600
I'd rather stay here, look after you,

350
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:05,040
watch you grow up.

351
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:08,680
See how high school life treats you.

352
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:11,600
Even if the exam results aren't great,

353
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,000
it's fine.

354
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,440
I'll always support you.

355
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:19,160
We'll wait for the day we can live together...

356
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:21,480
still orbiting around each other, right?

357
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,840
When do you have to return to Chiang Mai?

358
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:42,680
In two months, after the hundredth day of my mom’s passing.

359
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:46,640
Just hypothetically,

360
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,480
If I don’t pass any exams

361
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:53,280
and we don't end up living together,

362
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:54,960
would you be sad?

363
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,640
Yeah, I’d be.

364
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:01,480
The last time I left you, I was very upset.

365
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,480
Especially when you didn't read my texts on the way back,

366
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,360
it hit me even harder.

367
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:12,120
I hate seeing you upset or hurt.

368
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:16,680
I really wanted Champ out of your life for good,

369
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:23,560
But during Mom's funeral, Champ actually helped me a lot.

370
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:30,360
Back then, I should've used the money you gave
to fly over and be with you.

371
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:34,800
I want to know how you're doing. Can you eat?

372
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,840
Are you sleeping okay? I'm really worried.

373
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:39,160
I'm very worried about you.

374
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,440
I'm okay now.

375
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:45,240
That day when Mom went to see you,

376
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:48,760
what did you guys talk about?

377
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:51,240
Why did she suddenly agree to let me live with you?

378
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:53,360
Not telling. It's a secret.

379
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:58,840
Hey, I even spilled about the principal's office incident.

380
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:01,880
Change the subject...

381
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:04,480
How about this? My turn to ask.

382
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,880
Hypothetically...

383
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:10,120
What if I changed my mind and went to America?

384
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:14,160
But you just told me today you're not going, right?

385
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:16,800
Just hypothetically.

386
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,520
I'd be heartbroken,

387
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,920
especially after what you said after my exam.

388
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:36,720
So sad that you cried, like real tears?

389
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:39,880
I'm not you.

390
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:43,200
ince we've known each other, you've cried way more than me.

391
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:46,120
True, but I've never seen you cry.

392
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:49,160
Are tears rare for you?

393
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,920
Do you remember the last time you cried?

394
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:57,000
Maybe when I was little... when my granny died.

395
00:32:57,680 --> 00:33:01,560
You should let your tears out when you're sad. It helps.

396
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:03,560
Nah,

397
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:07,280
I guess I haven't felt sad enough to cry yet.

398
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:12,840
You really are tough, just like your dad said.

399
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:27,000
Back to your hypothetical question...

400
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:31,480
Are you still unsure about going to America?

401
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:34,040
Is that it?

402
00:33:35,520 --> 00:33:39,040
Well... I did apply,

403
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:41,040
but I doubt I'll get in.

404
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:43,640
What? But mom said you weren’t going.

405
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:52,120
Yeah, actually your mom helped me with the application.

406
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:57,640
So, if you do get it, would you really pass up the chance?

407
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:00,240
I might.

408
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:04,160
If I have to move there, it's worrying.

409
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,320
Going there for five years,

410
00:34:06,920 --> 00:34:09,159
and maybe longer if I land a job.

411
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:13,520
Some scholarship recipients even got to work at NASA.

412
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:17,520
But not going would be a huge letdown for me.

413
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:22,760
It's these worries that keep me on the fence.

414
00:34:27,719 --> 00:34:28,719
Quiet, huh?

415
00:34:29,080 --> 00:34:30,480
When did you submit your application?

416
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:33,360
Right at the deadline.

417
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:37,520
After I applied for my exam?

418
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:41,360
Tod...

419
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:44,320
I haven't made up my mind about going.

420
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,560
But doing this feels like a betrayal.

421
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,600
Okay, sorry about that.

422
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:01,080
What can I do to make it up to you?

423
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:04,000
No need to. It's just the way things are.

424
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:08,400
Come on Tod, don't be upset.

425
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:13,560
Fine, fine. I'll drop by next week.

426
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:16,600
Which day? Tell me the day.

427
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:18,400
Saturday. I'll stay the night,

428
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,600
-the entire night.
-For two nights?

429
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:24,160
Alright, two nights then.

430
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:28,640
And promise you won't go to America.

431
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:34,080
Okay, I promise I won’t go.

432
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:00,960
Hello?

433
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:03,400
Yes, it's me.

434
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:05,320
This is Todsaphon's mom.

435
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:08,680
Yes!

436
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:11,800
From Thawiwat Sueksa School, right?

437
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:17,640
Yes, thank you very much.

438
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:34,000
Hey, Tod. What's going on? I'm teaching, will call back...

439
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:37,120
Nick, I flunked the test.

440
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:40,560
Oh... really

441
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:44,520
[Nick to his student]
Terd, read this for now, I'll be back soon.

442
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,920
Now what do I do?

443
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:53,680
Did you try applying somewhere else? Maybe you'll get lucky...

444
00:36:58,040 --> 00:37:00,960
I think I won’t go live with you.

445
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:09,520
You said you wanted to see me grow.

446
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:15,080
I also want to know what my life will be like in high school.

447
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:21,800
It might be better if I stay with my parents.

448
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:28,680
You passed the exam. The school called to inform.

449
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:33,560
Aren’t you happy, Mom?

450
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:39,360
Nick also got a scholarship in the States,

451
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:42,440
but he said he'd turn it down...

452
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:47,600
If he was going to reject, he should have done it already.

453
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:53,560
Still haven't seen his decision,

454
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:56,640
not sure what he's waiting for.

455
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:14,640
He never told me he got the scholarship.

456
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:22,160
And he recently said

457
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:26,040
even if he did, he'd reject it.

458
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:48,960
I think Nick should go to America.

459
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:51,920
Don’t worry about me.

460
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:56,320
I can stay comfortably with my parents.

461
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:02,400
Let's just say... we have tried our best.

462
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:09,120
But I promised you that I wouldn't go.

463
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:14,640
If you weren't going, you would've said no by now.

464
00:39:17,240 --> 00:39:19,360
I know you're eager to go.

465
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:22,080
Just go.

466
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:27,680
It might be time for Pluto...

467
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:30,920
to become part of the solar system again.

468
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:40,640
I'm sorry I didn't cry.

469
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:46,160
But no tears doesn't mean I'm not upset.

470
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:49,280
I get it, really.

471
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:11,680
Go as far as you can.

472
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:14,840
Go to the farthest reaches of the universe.

473
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:17,160
If you encounter a black hole,

474
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:20,800
I'll be waiting for you at the event horizon.

475
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:24,880
And what if I don't go after all?

476
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:28,440
Then come back.

477
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:33,440
Don't forget, there are black holes in Thailand too.

478
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:36,760
Like Tod's black hole, right here...

479
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:13,560
[Present]

480
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:15,320
Spray some on me too.

481
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:17,920
-Doesn't smell bad now?
-Nope, not at all.

482
00:41:18,680 --> 00:41:20,160
You can bathe me too.

483
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:23,040
Oh, wait a sec!

484
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:28,680
-Here, some snacks.
-Alirght.

485
00:41:31,680 --> 00:41:32,480
Kun!

486
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:33,800
Huh?

487
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:38,600
Actually, I passed the exam that day.

488
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,000
Oh!

489
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:48,480
Then why did you tell me you failed?

490
00:41:52,840 --> 00:41:53,880
There were several reasons.

491
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,720
Wanted to stay with my folks,

492
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,080
and...

493
00:42:03,560 --> 00:42:05,320
Was it because of that guy who visited us?

494
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:07,160
Yes!

495
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:17,240
Still in touch with him?

496
00:42:22,760 --> 00:42:23,840
Not much.

497
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:28,240
He must be busy with studies.

498
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:31,240
He only replies occasionally.

499
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:35,040
That's not strange.

500
00:42:36,120 --> 00:42:37,560
These days, I'm also talking to many people.

501
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:39,920
Chatting and then they disappear.

502
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:42,440
Maybe they're in another world.

503
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:48,080
An hour for us might be seven years for them.

504
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,320
Kun!

505
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:00,600
Sorry, dude,

506
00:43:01,640 --> 00:43:02,960
for everything that's happened.

507
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:09,960
It's okay.

508
00:43:11,480 --> 00:43:13,040
Being friends is great, right?

509
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:17,360
I understand.

510
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:22,480
Hearing your story about him,

511
00:43:24,480 --> 00:43:25,640
I understand now.

512
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:31,280
No wonder you still miss him.

513
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:41,200
You know what...

514
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:44,520
If back then...

515
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:49,280
I had known it was our last meeting,

516
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:52,520
I would've...

517
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:56,280
So, haven't seen him since?

518
00:44:00,520 --> 00:44:01,320
Nope.

519
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:06,520
He took the scholarship at the last minute

520
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:12,760
and flew out a few weeks later.

521
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:18,160
He said he’d come

522
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:21,200
but never showed up in the end.

523
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:36,280
You were really angry at the principal then, right?

524
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:39,400
Everyone at school gossiped about it,

525
00:44:40,680 --> 00:44:42,520
especially after that science lab video leaked.

526
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:46,920
Actually,

